<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicName LSID="F29764A8-B47D-5855-B726-4F818CD797AC" authority="Bunge in Boiss., Fl. Orient. 4: 912 (1879)." authorityName="Bunge in Boiss., Fl. Orient. 4: 912" authorityYear="1879" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="Atriplex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Atriplex flabellum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flabellum">Atriplex flabellum Bunge in Boiss., Fl. Orient. 4: 912 (1879).</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="Obione" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Obione flabellum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flabellum">Obione flabellum</taxonomicName>
≡ 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="Obione" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Obione flabellum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flabellum">Obione flabellum</taxonomicName>
(Bunge) Ulbr. in Engler &amp; Prantl, Nat. Pflanzenfam., ed. 2, 16c: 506 (1934). Type: Iran. &quot;Persia, in montosis salsis ad orientem urbis Meschhed, inter Faz et Tabatkuh prov. Khorassan&quot;, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">A. Bunge</emphasis>
(LE!, lectotype designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sukhorukov, AP" journalOrPublisher="Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" refId="B25" refString="Sukhorukov, AP, 2006. Zur Systematik und Chorologie der in Russland und den benachbarten Staaten (in den Grenzen der ehemaligen USSR) vorkommenden Atriplex-Arten (Chenopodiaceae). Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien 108 B: 307-420." title="Zur Systematik und Chorologie der in Russland und den benachbarten Staaten (in den Grenzen der ehemaligen USSR) vorkommenden Atriplex-Arten (Chenopodiaceae). Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien 108 B: 307 - 420." year="2006">Sukhorukov (2006</bibRefCitation>
: 408)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="morphology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Morphology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
For a detailed description, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Iljin, MM" editor="Shishkin, BK" journalOrPublisher="6. Academy of Sciences of the USSR, Moscow &amp; Leningrad" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" pagination="2 - 354" refId="B11" refString="Iljin, MM, 1936. Chenopodiaceae. In: Shishkin, BK, Ed., Flora of the USSR, Vol. 6. Academy of Sciences of the USSR, Moscow &amp; Leningrad: 2 - 354" title="Chenopodiaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of the USSR, Vol." year="1936">Iljin (1936)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hedge, IC" editor="Rechinger, KH" journalOrPublisher="197. Akademische Druck- und Verlagsanstalt, Graz" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" pagination="63 - 87" refId="B8" refString="Hedge, IC, 1997. Atriplex. In: Rechinger, KH, Ed., Flora Iranica, Vol. 197. Akademische Druck- und Verlagsanstalt, Graz: 63 - 87" title="Atriplex." volumeTitle="Flora Iranica, Vol." year="1997">Hedge (1997)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Sukhorukov, AP" journalOrPublisher="Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" refId="B25" refString="Sukhorukov, AP, 2006. Zur Systematik und Chorologie der in Russland und den benachbarten Staaten (in den Grenzen der ehemaligen USSR) vorkommenden Atriplex-Arten (Chenopodiaceae). Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien 108 B: 307-420." title="Zur Systematik und Chorologie der in Russland und den benachbarten Staaten (in den Grenzen der ehemaligen USSR) vorkommenden Atriplex-Arten (Chenopodiaceae). Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien 108 B: 307 - 420." year="2006">Sukhorukov (2006)</bibRefCitation>
. The species is recognisable in all stages by its (sub)opposite crenate leaves with the Kranz-type anatomy, and flabellate and stalked bract-like covers of the female flowers with ventrally fused valves. The (sub)opposite leaves are very rarely found in the C4-clade of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="Atriplex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Atriplex" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Atriplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the ventral valve fusion is present only in two Eurasian species of the genus, 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. flabellum" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="flabellum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">A. flabellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. moneta" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="moneta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">A. moneta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="specimen seen">
